#: ../../../advanced/tensor-memory-accelerator.md:1
msgid "Tensor Memory Accelerator (TMA)"
msgstr "張量記憶體加速器（TMA）"

#: ../../../advanced/tensor-memory-accelerator.md:3
msgid ""
"Starting with the Hopper architecture (SM 90), NVIDIA GPUs include a "
"dedicated hardware unit — the **Tensor Memory Accelerator** — that moves "
"data between global and shared memory *without* occupying thread execution "
"resources. Instead of every thread in a block issuing its own load "
"instruction, a single thread hands a descriptor to the TMA engine, and the "
"hardware performs the entire transfer asynchronously. The other 127 threads "
"are free to compute, load other data, or simply wait at a barrier."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced/tensor-memory-accelerator.md:11
msgid ""
"cuda-oxide exposes TMA through `TmaDescriptor`, the `cp_async_bulk_tensor_*` "
"family, and the `ManagedBarrier` typestate API. This chapter covers the "
"setup, the copy patterns, and how TMA integrates with barriers to build "
"efficient load/compute pipelines."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced/tensor-memory-accelerator.md:17
msgid ""
"[CUDA Programming Guide — Asynchronous Data Copies using TMA](https://docs."
"nvidia.com/cuda/cuda-programming-guide/#tensor-memory-access) for a complete "
"description of the hardware unit, swizzle modes, and supported tensor "
"dimensions."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced/tensor-memory-accelerator.md:24
msgid "The problem TMA solves"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced/tensor-memory-accelerator.md:26
msgid ""
"In the [Shared Memory](shared-memory-and-synchronization.md) chapter, every "
"thread in the block participates in loading a tile from global memory:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced/tensor-memory-accelerator.md:29
msgid "TILE_A[ty * TILE + tx] = a[row * k + tile_offset + tx];\n"
msgstr "TILE_A[ty * TILE + tx] = a[row * k + tile_offset + tx];\n"

#: ../../../advanced/tensor-memory-accelerator.md:33
msgid ""
"This works, but it means all 128 (or 256, or 1024) threads in the block "
"spend time computing addresses and issuing load instructions. For large "
"tiles, the load phase can dominate the kernel's runtime."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced/tensor-memory-accelerator.md:37
msgid ""
"TMA replaces the per-thread load loop with a single hardware instruction. "
"One thread says \"copy this 2D region from global to shared,\" and the TMA "
"engine handles the rest — including address computation, stride handling, "
"and bank-conflict-free swizzled writes."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced/tensor-memory-accelerator.md:46
msgid ""
"TMA async bulk copy pipeline. The host builds a `TmaDescriptor` encoding the "
"tensor's layout. On the device, one thread issues the copy and all threads "
"wait on an mbarrier. The TMA engine performs the transfer asynchronously, "
"signals the barrier on completion, and threads proceed to compute from "
"shared memory."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced/tensor-memory-accelerator.md:55
msgid "TmaDescriptor — the tensor map"
msgstr "TmaDescriptor — 張量映射"

#: ../../../advanced/tensor-memory-accelerator.md:57
msgid ""
"A `TmaDescriptor` is a 128-byte opaque struct that encodes everything the "
"TMA engine needs to know about a tensor: base address, dimensions, element "
"type, stride, and swizzle mode. It is built on the **host** using the CUDA "
"driver API:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced/tensor-memory-accelerator.md:62
msgid ""
"use cuda_device::tma::TmaDescriptor;\n"
"\n"
"// On the host (simplified — the real call has many parameters)\n"
"unsafe {\n"
"    cuTensorMapEncodeTiled(\n"
"        &mut desc as *mut TmaDescriptor as *mut _,\n"
"        CU_TENSOR_MAP_DATA_TYPE_FLOAT32,\n"
"        2,                       // 2D tensor\n"
"        global_ptr,              // base address in global memory\n"
"        &dims,                   // [rows, cols]\n"
"        &strides,                // byte strides per dimension\n"
"        &box_dims,               // tile size per copy\n"
"        &elem_strides,           // element strides within a box\n"
"        CU_TENSOR_MAP_INTERLEAVE_NONE,\n"
"        CU_TENSOR_MAP_SWIZZLE_128B, // bank-conflict-free swizzle\n"
"        CU_TENSOR_MAP_L2_PROMOTION_L2_128B,\n"
"        CU_TENSOR_MAP_FLOAT_OOB_FILL_NONE,\n"
"    );\n"
"}\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced/tensor-memory-accelerator.md:84
msgid ""
"The descriptor is then passed to the kernel as a regular argument. On the "
"device, it is treated as `*const TmaDescriptor` — opaque, read-only, and "
"always valid for the lifetime of the allocation it describes."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced/tensor-memory-accelerator.md:89
msgid ""
"The swizzle mode is the most performance-critical parameter. `SWIZZLE_128B` "
"rearranges the byte layout in shared memory so that 128-byte accesses from "
"different warps hit different banks. Without swizzling, naive 2D tile loads "
"often produce bank conflicts."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced/tensor-memory-accelerator.md:97
msgid "Global-to-shared copies (G2S)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced/tensor-memory-accelerator.md:99
msgid ""
"The `cp_async_bulk_tensor_*_g2s` functions issue a TMA copy from global "
"memory into a shared memory destination. They are available for 1D through "
"5D tensors:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced/tensor-memory-accelerator.md:103
msgid ""
"use cuda_device::tma::{cp_async_bulk_tensor_2d_g2s, TmaDescriptor};\n"
"use cuda_device::barrier::Barrier;\n"
"\n"
"unsafe fn load_tile(\n"
"    smem_dst: *mut u8,\n"
"    desc: *const TmaDescriptor,\n"
"    tile_x: i32,\n"
"    tile_y: i32,\n"
"    bar: *mut Barrier,\n"
") {\n"
"    cp_async_bulk_tensor_2d_g2s(smem_dst, desc, tile_x, tile_y, bar);\n"
"}\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced/tensor-memory-accelerator.md:118
msgid ""
"The coordinates (`tile_x`, `tile_y`) specify which tile to copy, in units of "
"the box dimensions encoded in the descriptor. The barrier pointer tells the "
"TMA engine where to signal completion."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced/tensor-memory-accelerator.md:122
msgid "Only one thread issues the copy"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced/tensor-memory-accelerator.md:124
msgid ""
"TMA copies are **not** collective operations across the block. Exactly **one "
"thread** should call `cp_async_bulk_tensor_*_g2s`. All other threads "
"participate through the barrier mechanism:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced/tensor-memory-accelerator.md:128
msgid ""
"if thread::threadIdx_x() == 0 {\n"
"    let token = bar.arrive_expect_tx(tile_bytes as u32);\n"
"    unsafe {\n"
"        cp_async_bulk_tensor_2d_g2s(dst, desc, x, y, bar.as_ptr() as *mut "
"_);\n"
"    }\n"
"    bar.wait(token);\n"
"} else {\n"
"    let token = bar.arrive();\n"
"    bar.wait(token);\n"
"}\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced/tensor-memory-accelerator.md:141
msgid ""
"`arrive_expect_tx(bytes)` tells the barrier to expect an additional `bytes` "
"worth of transaction completions beyond the thread arrivals. The barrier "
"trips when all threads have arrived *and* the TMA engine has delivered all "
"expected bytes."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced/tensor-memory-accelerator.md:148
msgid "The mbarrier dance"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced/tensor-memory-accelerator.md:150
msgid ""
"TMA completion tracking relies on `ManagedBarrier` (or the raw `mbarrier_*` "
"functions). The typestate API enforces the lifecycle at the type level:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced/tensor-memory-accelerator.md:153
msgid ""
"use cuda_device::barrier::{Barrier, ManagedBarrier, TmaBarrierHandle, "
"Uninit, Ready};\n"
"use cuda_device::SharedArray;\n"
"\n"
"#[kernel]\n"
"pub fn tma_load_kernel(desc: *const TmaDescriptor) {\n"
"    static mut BAR: SharedArray<Barrier, 1, 128> = SharedArray::UNINIT;\n"
"\n"
"    let bar: TmaBarrierHandle<Ready> = unsafe {\n"
"        TmaBarrierHandle::<Uninit>::from_static(BAR.as_mut_ptr())\n"
"            .init_by(block_size, 0) // thread 0 inits, includes fence + "
"sync\n"
"    };\n"
"\n"
"    // Issue TMA copy\n"
"    if thread::threadIdx_x() == 0 {\n"
"        let token = bar.arrive_expect_tx(TILE_BYTES as u32);\n"
"        unsafe {\n"
"            cp_async_bulk_tensor_2d_g2s(\n"
"                smem_ptr, desc, tile_x, tile_y, bar.as_ptr() as *mut _\n"
"            );\n"
"        }\n"
"        bar.wait(token);\n"
"    } else {\n"
"        let token = bar.arrive();\n"
"        bar.wait(token);\n"
"    }\n"
"\n"
"    // Shared memory now contains the tile — safe to read\n"
"    // ...\n"
"\n"
"    unsafe { bar.inval(); }\n"
"}\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced/tensor-memory-accelerator.md:187
msgid ""
"The lifecycle is: `Uninit` → `init()` → `Ready` → `arrive()` / `wait()` → "
"`inval()` → `Invalidated`. The type system prevents calling `wait` on an "
"uninitialized barrier or `arrive` on an invalidated one."
msgstr ""

