#: ../../../advanced/tensor-memory-accelerator.md:202
msgid "Shared-to-global copies (S2G)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced/tensor-memory-accelerator.md:204
msgid ""
"TMA also supports the reverse direction. The pattern uses commit groups "
"instead of barriers:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced/tensor-memory-accelerator.md:207
msgid ""
"use cuda_device::tma::{\n"
"    cp_async_bulk_tensor_2d_s2g,\n"
"    cp_async_bulk_commit_group,\n"
"    cp_async_bulk_wait_group,\n"
"};\n"
"\n"
"unsafe {\n"
"    cp_async_bulk_tensor_2d_s2g(smem_src, desc, tile_x, tile_y);\n"
"    cp_async_bulk_commit_group();\n"
"    cp_async_bulk_wait_group(0); // wait for all outstanding groups\n"
"}\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced/tensor-memory-accelerator.md:221
msgid ""
"S2G copies do not use barriers. Instead, `commit_group` bundles outstanding "
"copies into a group, and `wait_group(n)` blocks until at most `n` groups "
"remain in flight. `wait_group(0)` waits for everything."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced/tensor-memory-accelerator.md:227
msgid "Alignment requirements"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced/tensor-memory-accelerator.md:229
msgid ""
"TMA destinations in shared memory must be **128-byte aligned**. cuda-oxide "
"provides this through the `ALIGN` parameter on `SharedArray` and "
"`DynamicSharedArray`:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced/tensor-memory-accelerator.md:233
msgid ""
"static mut TILE: SharedArray<f32, 1024, 128> = SharedArray::UNINIT;\n"
"\n"
"// Or with dynamic shared memory:\n"
"let dst: *mut u8 = DynamicSharedArray::<u8, 128>::get();\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced/tensor-memory-accelerator.md:240
msgid ""
"If the destination is not 128-byte aligned, the TMA engine will silently "
"produce incorrect results or fault. There is no runtime check — the "
"alignment must be correct by construction."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced/tensor-memory-accelerator.md:246
msgid "Multicast variants"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced/tensor-memory-accelerator.md:248
msgid ""
"On Hopper+ with clusters enabled, TMA can multicast a single global load "
"into the shared memory of multiple CTAs simultaneously:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced/tensor-memory-accelerator.md:251
msgid ""
"use cuda_device::tma::cp_async_bulk_tensor_2d_g2s_multicast;\n"
"\n"
"unsafe {\n"
"    cp_async_bulk_tensor_2d_g2s_multicast(\n"
"        dst, desc, x, y, bar_ptr,\n"
"        cta_mask,  // u16 bitmask of target CTAs in the cluster\n"
"    );\n"
"}\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced/tensor-memory-accelerator.md:262
msgid ""
"This is particularly useful for GEMM-style kernels where the same tile of A "
"or B is needed by multiple thread blocks. Instead of each block loading its "
"own copy, one TMA operation serves all of them."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced/tensor-memory-accelerator.md:267
msgid ""
"[Cluster Programming](cluster-programming.md) for the full cluster model and "
"distributed shared memory, which pairs naturally with TMA multicast."
msgstr ""

